    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Case of Wen Ho Lee: The Questions Linger</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Betty Lee Sung letter says real culprit in case of Wen Ho Lee and stolen nuclear secrets is widespread perception that China has replaced Soviet Union as nation's primary antagonist</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Times and Wen Ho Lee'' (Note ''From the Editors,'' Sept. 26):</p>
        <p>A lot of finger-pointing is taking place for the harsh, unjust and unequal treatment of Wen Ho Lee by government officials. The New York Times is being blamed, too. But the real culprit is the widespread perception that China has replaced the Soviet Union as this country's primary antagonist.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Times and Wen Ho Lee'' (Note ''From the Editors,'' Sept. 26):</p>
        <p>A lot of finger-pointing is taking place for the harsh, unjust and unequal treatment of Wen Ho Lee by government officials. The New York Times is being blamed, too. But the real culprit is the widespread perception that China has replaced the Soviet Union as this country's primary antagonist.</p>
        <p>A corollary is the linking of Chinese-Americans to Chinese politics and Chinese-American relations.  Consequently, Chinese-Americans are suspects and targets for whatever happens in bilateral relations.  You would do a great service by helping to correct the perceptions that China is an enemy and that Chinese-Americans are tainted because they are ethnic Chinese.  BETTY LEE SUNG  New York, Sept. 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
